vel_probabilities":{"Unit":0.33,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When memory usage exceeds the configured threshold, the eviction strategy switches from LRU to LFU as specified in the configuration.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at module boundary between memory-pressure signal, config threshold, and strategy selector/state manager. A unit test of selector logic alone can miss wiring/state propagation bugs. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: behavior text does not require real OS memory APIs; threshold crossing can be reproduced in-process. No AI dependency or multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run cache manager with real strategy-selection wiring, feed memory-usage telemetry around threshold, and assert active strategy transitions LRU->LFU per config (including hysteresis/edge equality behavior if defined).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A write to the underlying PostgreSQL table invalidates all cache entries whose keys match the affected rows.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module consistency behavior: DB write path/event handling + key mapping + invalidation fan-out. MOCK-HIDE: mocking DB writes/events can miss contract mismatches in change payload mapping. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: requires DB interaction, but a local PostgreSQL instance/local DB integration is enough; no OS/network-specific failure artifact is explicitly required by behavior text. No AI dependency and no multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"With cache layer and DB-change invalidation path wired together against a local Postgres test instance, seed cache entries for multiple rows, perform row updates/inserts/deletes, then assert only keys matching affected rows are invalidated and unrelated keys remain.","plan_consisten